RACE.FOOTNOTES: BRIEF travelled near the rear three wide outside of her rivals down the back straight, began to lengthen stride quickly moving in on the leaders around the far bend, pounced to the lead four wide straightening out for home and drew away when roused in the final furlong. SPIRIT O'TIPPERARY stalked near the back on the rail at the half, shifted just outside off the fence with five sixteenths to go passing horses, swung out to be five wide extending her stride smartly turning for home and was no match for the winner down the lane but finished up well to be a clear second on this day. HIGH TREASON stalked near the rear between horses down the backside, commenced her run closing in on others midway on the final turn, angled outside to the five path for the drive and gamely prevailed for the show battle. TAKE CHANCES co-trailed on the outside at the half, began to rally around runners three wide on the far turn, swung out widest in the six path with run at the top of the stretch and dueled for third to the wire just losing the photo in the end. FOREVER DANISH tracked the front two into the first turn, continued rating comfortably waiting for her que down the backstretch, began to close in on the leaders at the three furlong marker, briefly had the lead between foes in upper stretch and stalled in the final sixteenth never switching leads. SMOKEN CHLOE stumbled on the break, recovered to have a nice tracking position outside runners in midfield down the backside, was roused for more at the three eighths marker, put in a mild run on the fence until the top of the lane and faded inside in deep stretch. SEATTLE SIGNAL took this field into the first turn, continued to dictate the pace unchallenged down the backside, was collared outside by rivals in upper stretch, offered no resistance and folded in the last sixteenth. QUEEN OF THE COURT co-trailed on the inside down the back straight, saved all the ground but could not get involved running around the final bend and was not a factor in the stretch drive. QUEEN SAHARA chased the pace down the backstretch, was roused trying to keep up with the frontrunner three furlongs out, had no more to offer on the far turn and backed away through the field at the quarter pole.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: ROCKET JOE COPPER rated in behind the leaders, bided time into the far turn, moved out and took the lead three wide and between foes by the quarter pole, drew clear in upper stretch, was kept busy to the wire and held. ROCKLAND EXPRESS was in just a hair tight between runners at the start while receiving a light brush, settled two to three wide off the pace, advanced on the far turn swinging seven wide for the stretch run, drifted in a path in mid-stretch then straightened out and continued to gain steadily on the winner but needed more. CHELSEA DAGGER bumped lightly with a rival at the start, settled off the pace moving up to mid-pack racing near but off the rail, came out for the stretch run in range, drifted out nearing the sixteenth pole and steadied on heels, ran on for show. KODIAK MAMBA (IRE) settled toward the back three to four deep, swung out a bit into upper stretch then shifted out further to be nine wide at the furlong marker, kicked on mildly. QUIET REBEL stumbled at the start, was under a hold inside at the back early, came off the inside on the far turn, passed tired rivals. THY KINGDOM raced outside four to five wide at the rear, failed to menace. ROCK BULLET stalked near the rear down the backstretch, began to uncork a rally three wide midway on the far turn ,loomed in the five path outside rivals at the top of the lane, drifted inwards under right handed encouragement driving to the finish at the sixteenth pole and just missed getting up at the line. HEY LUIGI prompted the pace outside down the backstretch, closed in to bid between horses in the three path turning for home, stubbornly dueled with rivals on each side to the wire, was steadied in tight quarters at the sixteenth pole and could not offer a finish afterwards. RACE.FOOTNOTES: MISTER MESEEKS settled three wide at the back, advanced five to six deep, fanned seven wide into upper stretch, bid in mid-stretch, drifted in a path while clear, prevailed under steady handling. COACH ABERNATHY took back and tucked in early racing two wide at the back into the first turn, advanced near but off the rail on the far turn, moved out five wide coming to the top of the stretch, was bumped lightly in mid-stretch, kept on for the place. TWIXTER settled three to four wide early moving out five wide on the first turn, advanced on the far turn three deep shifting five wide into upper stretch, exchanged light bumps while drifting out near the furlong grounds and kept on. HIP TO YOUR TRICKS set the early tempo from inside on or just off the rail, was overtaken leaving the first turn but still stalked from inside just off the fence, regained the lead past the three-eighths, was clear coming to the quarter pole, drifted out a bit into upper stretch, was overtaken and outkicked. SOCIAL JUSTICE settled inside toward the back, advanced while coming out off the fence on the far turn, continued to progress in the stretch coming in just a bit near the sixteenth and kept on. GOOD SOLDIER received a saddle adjustment behind the gate, settled outside at the back four to five wide, advanced still in the same path through the far turn into upper stretch, was in range between runners, clipped heels in mid-stretch stumbling and ran on. GLENHOLME was caught outside foes four then six wide in the early going, moved up some into the far turn, was carried nine wide by the drifting and tiring lead late on that bend, ran on. CHAIRMAN LAYLA tracked from inside mid-pack, steadied slightly at the sixteenth pole when in just a hair tight. READY ON THE LINE forced the pace from outside while kept four deep and drifting to the six path on the first turn, had a clear advantage up the backstretch still racing wide and entering the far turn in the four path, drifted eight wide while weakening late on that bend, came up empty. SILENT WARNING chased three to four wide early, dropped back between runners entering the far turn, tired. FOLLOWING A STEWARDS' INQUIRY INVOLVING TWIXTER IN THE STRETCH AS WELL AS AN OBJECTION BY THE RIDER OF CHAIRMAN LAYLA AGAINST SOCIAL JUSTICE AND AN OBJECTION BY THE RIDER OF GOOD SOLDIER AGAINST MISTER MESEEKS ALLEGING INTERFERENCE, THE TWO OBJECTIONS WERE NOT ALLOWED BUT TWIXTER WAS DISQUALIFIED FROM THIRD AND PLACED SIXTH BEHIND GOOD SOLDIER FOR CAUSING A REACTION LEADING TO THE LATTER CLIPPING HEELS IN MID-STRETCH.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: JIM'S HOPE travelled in midfield on the outside of horses down the backside, took closer order tracking three deep at the half, pounced three wide midpoint on the far turn, cleared away in mid-stretch and was kept to the task to hold safe at the finish. RAPID TEST stalked near the rear in the early stages, was roused for more three eighths from the line but did not quicken with others, could see the field at the top of the stretch and finally found another gear bursting by runners swinging out to the six path at the furlong pole to nab the place award at the wire. SOUPED UP had a good spot nestled behind the pacesetter down the backside, waited patiently behind the wall of the contesting front three runners at the quarter pole, angled in to the two path turning for home, battled stubbornly to the wire just missing out on holding for place in the end. CHASING TROUBLE co-trailed on the outside down the back straight, advanced three wide around foes with five sixteenths to run, loomed a threat outside in the five path straightening out for the drive but stalled late, losing a couple of placings at the wire. POULIN IN O T set a modest pace at the half, was collared outside by runners midway on the far turn, bravely fought on through the lane until the furlong marker and faded in deep stretch. GUNS N' ROJAS was allowed to settle trailing the field down the backstretch, saved ground advancing smartly through the far turn, was in range for a share on the fence at the top of the lane but could not offer a finishing bid to the wire. SILENT MIRACLE kept a close eye on the leader down the backstretch, bid for the lead in the two path with rivals on each side at the quarter pole, could not find more turning for home and yielded in mid-stretch.

WICKEDBLACKBULLET tracked on the rail down the backside, made a sharp move on the the turn to battle for the lead on the fence at the quarter marker, could no match strides with the winner down the stretch and easily bested the rest at the finish in a solid effort. MR. RUDY took a commanding lead down the backstretch, was engulfed on each side at the quarter pole, could not go on with the top pair turning for home and gamely finished up to hold safe for third money at the wire. DIXIE'S FLATTER trailed the field down the back straight, began to pick up rivals on the outside two furlongs from the prize, angled out to the four path for the stretch drive and closed smartly for a minor role down the lane. TONKA WAKAN stalked near the back early on, improved down the backside, began to creep closer to rivals running around the bend and was one paced through the stretch making little presence. HOLIDAY IN CHILE stalked near the rear down the backside, was hard ridden on the fence through the turn, was in with a chance for a minor share inside turning for home but could not offer a finish down the stretch. WONT FORGET YOU broke outwards at the start, stalked in midfield outside at the half, offered a brief run splitting rivals around the bend, was in with a chance for a small share turning for home but faltered in the final furlong. ROYAL CHROME had a good position on the outside keeping track of the front two down the backstretch, was roused but could not quicken with others on the turn and retreated six wide in upper stretch. AUTUMN'S SO FLASHY ducked in sharply at the start, dislodged the rider and walked off back to the barn.
